 ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaauminki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aauminki</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 991<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 6:24:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1115.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on complete heal rotations</span><hr size=1> Just throwing some ideas out here, different things work for different guilds <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br><br>DA the clerics after first CH land - don't wait till the cleric gets summoned, just do it rightaway - bard can do also if you want, BDA is really good since it's insta cast<br><br>Rely on patch heals to last the first couple of rounds, DL/Sup Heals/NT/LoH etc. and DI <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19405 target=blank>Marshall Sscaley Iceblade</a><br><i><a href=http://companions.windsofstorm.net>The Companions</a></i> <br>Warlizard on Tribunal</big><br><small>"Tails are not for biting or pulling!"</small></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usharak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 7:07:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1115.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ldguild.net/ldnews/images/dollz/sharakaidollz.gif HEIGHT=160 WIDTH=140></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on complete heal rotations</span><hr size=1> Patch heals are great.<br><br>However, growing a great about of initial contact aggro is your best bet.  On a mob that will come roaring down on you quadding for 4k a pop, you need to stick it to you as soon as humanly possible.  Dirty aggro tricks will only get your guild killed (such as AE taunt off a superaggro Ranger weaponshielded, etc).<br><br>Save yourself the trouble and pop off snare glands.  Or, if you are quick enough, AE taunt off that first CH if the mob turns (err.. better to rely on the glands).<br><br>Hate reduction spells on the first cleric in the rotation is nice, as well as hate production spell on your tank (if you can fit it).<br><br>Oh, do not ever ever ever rely on DI.<br><br>Honestly though.  I havent seen a mob turn on one of our cleric at first CH in a very very long time.  Dunno why.  They locked me out of the cleric channel cause I have a tendancy to spam it with /2 OMG HELP HELP HEAL ME!  OH JEEZ IT HURTS!  MOMMY!  HEAAAAALLL MEEEEEE!! <p>Sharak'Duom 51 Ghost<br>Keroppi'Duom 60 Godzilla<br>Sharakai'Duom 59 Ronin<br><center><a href="http://www.ldguild.net"><img src="http://www.ldguild.net/ldnews/images/dollz/ldbanner.gif" alt="Lumiere Divine, Zebuxoruk" border="0"></A></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usularusglorybringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sularus Glorybringer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.superior.net/~markf/babypics/sos/us.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 10:26:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1115.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on complete heal rotations</span><hr size=1> We usually have the back-up healers(druids, shaman, pally) spam Gheals, Sheals, Chloroblast, etc.  Works great for spreading aggro and keeping it on the MT and off the First CH cleric.<br><br> <p><i><b><a target=new href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=53389>Sularus GloryBringer</a></b></i>Knight of Mithaniel Marr, the Truthbringer<br>Bringer of his Glory on The Nameless<BR>Grand Master of <a target=_blank href=http://www.veratae.com>(Veratae's Blade)</a><BR>Bane of Evil & Protector of those who walk in the Light</i><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugimily.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gimily</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 1:34:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1115.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on complete heal rotations</span><hr size=1> Paladins burning a LoH right as the MT agro's helps too.<br><br>Using fast heals by all other healers accept the first CHer seems to be the best in my opinion.<br><br>Gimily Smashfist<br>60 Cleric (Retired)<br><br>Gimilly Smashfist<br>50 Warrior <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaiilchayser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaiilChayser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 2:33:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1115.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://us.f1.yahoofs.com/users/2cf0709f/bc/Everquest/Swords.gif?bc51WW9AIMPG2542 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on complete heal rotations</span><hr size=1> Aye do a LoH rotation (if you have multiple pallies as we do) first, then go with some patch heals before starting the CH rotation. <p><div align="center"><embed width="468" height="148" src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/amplified/SWSig.swf"></div><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unctrader.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nctrader</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/2/02 5:49:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1115.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on complete heal rotations</span><hr size=1> Having played a cleric for many levels I have conducted CH rotations in many ways.  It really depends on the mob your fighting, but one method for those hard hitters than double for 1k damage is to start out the CH rotation with a Pally using his LoH to avoid the inital aggro on the healing cleric, then the clerics kick in with the CH order.  Another way I've done a CH rotation is for clerics to start with Celestial Healing spells (Heals over time) until MA can establish a better hold on the hate list.  During the initial flurry of heals over time, the other healer type players will supplement with patch heals.  There will be overlap, but its better than having a  gap and possibly a wipe out. <p>Kodi - Cleric of the 54th Season - Battle Cry<BR>Bubbamac - Ogre Warrior of the 53rd Season - Battle Cry<BR> Yamar Asim - Paladin of the 51st Season - Battle Cry<BR> Tuunes - Bard of the 30th Season - Heart of the Dunedain<BR>Terris Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxenojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/3/02 1:28:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1115.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on complete heal rotations</span><hr size=1> If you are using spam healing at the beggining, as you should, make sure they are not getting on the rampage list doing so.<br><br><br><br>Rollen <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showPrevMessage?topicID=1115.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showNextMessage?topicID=1115.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1115.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.emailToFriend?topicID=1115.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.threadControl?topicID=1115.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br>